cuda_to_hip_mappings.py 
1    import collections
2    import os
3    
4    from .constants import (API_BLAS, API_C10, API_CAFFE2, API_DRIVER, API_FFT,
5                            API_PYTORCH, API_RAND, API_ROCTX, API_RTC, API_RUNTIME,
6                            API_SPECIAL, API_ROCMSMI, CONV_CACHE, CONV_CONTEXT, CONV_D3D9,
7                            CONV_D3D10, CONV_D3D11, CONV_DEF, CONV_DEVICE,
8                            CONV_DEVICE_FUNC, CONV_EGL, CONV_ERROR, CONV_EVENT,
9                            CONV_EXEC, CONV_GL, CONV_GRAPHICS, CONV_INCLUDE,
10                           CONV_INCLUDE_CUDA_MAIN_H, CONV_INIT, CONV_JIT,
11                           CONV_MATH_FUNC, CONV_MEM, CONV_MODULE,
12                           CONV_NUMERIC_LITERAL, CONV_OCCUPANCY, CONV_OTHER,
13                           CONV_PEER, CONV_SPECIAL_FUNC, CONV_STREAM,
14                           CONV_SURFACE, CONV_TEX, CONV_THREAD, CONV_TYPE,
15                           CONV_VDPAU, CONV_VERSION, HIP_UNSUPPORTED)
16   
17   """ Mapping of CUDA functions, include files, constants, and types to ROCm/HIP equivalents 
18   This closely follows the implementation in hipify-clang 
19   https://github.com/ROCm/hip/blob/59071b895ed1c86d9698b4c859cefcdd5acda06f/hipify-clang/src/CUDA2HipMap.cpp 
20   and its structure. 
21   There are different maps for fundamental names, include files, identifies, sparse, and 
22   PyTorch specific translations. 
23   Each of the entries in these maps translates a CUDA string to a tuple containing the 
24   ROCm/HIP string, a type and API annotation and - optionally - an annotation if it is not 
25   supported in ROCm/HIP yet. 
26   """
27   
28   _IS_FBCODE = os.environ.get("IS_FBCODE", "0") == "1"
29   
30   # FBCODE compiles against rccl sources instead of an installed rccl package.
31   # The header location is src/rccl.h versus rccl/rccl.h, respectively.
32   _RCCL_HEADER = "<rccl.h>" if _IS_FBCODE else "<rccl/rccl.h>"
33   
34   # List of math functions that should be replaced inside device code only.
35   MATH_TRANSPILATIONS = collections.OrderedDict(
36       [
37           ("std::max", ("::max")),
38           ("std::min", ("::min")),
39           ("std::ceil", ("::ceil")),
40           ("std::floor", ("::floor")),
41           ("std::exp", ("::exp")),
42           ("std::log", ("::log")),
43           ("std::pow", ("::pow")),
44           ("std::fabs", ("::fabs")),
45           ("std::fmod", ("::fmod")),
46           ("std::remainder", ("::remainder")),
47           ("std::frexp", ("::frexp")),
48       ]
49   )
50

8737 
8738 # We must tread very carefully here.  Blanket conversions like are done
8739 # in CAFFE2_SPECIFIC_MAPPINGS are not presently supported on PyTorch,
8740 # because a regex for CUDA will also match a filename like CUDAGuard.h,
8741 # but the HIPIFY script doesn't presently move the file and so the substitution
8742 # will be invalid.  Instead, we specifically list out every identifier
8743 # and file from c10/cuda which may be used externally, and do substitutions this
8744 # way.
8745 #
